org.numenta.nupic.util

Class GroupBy2<R extends java.lang.Comparable<R>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.numenta.nupic.util.GroupBy2<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - The return type of the user-provided Functions
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<Tuple>, java.util.Iterator<Tuple>, Generator<Tuple>

    public class GroupBy2<R extends java.lang.Comparable<R>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Generator<Tuple>
    An Java extension to groupby in Python's itertools. Allows to walk across n sorted lists with respect to their key functions and yields a Tuple of n lists of the members of the next *smallest* group.
    Author:
    cogmission

    • Method Detail

      • of

        public static <R extends java.lang.Comparable<R>> GroupBy2<R> of(<any>... entries)

        Returns a GroupBy2 instance which is used to group lists of objects in ascending order using keys supplied by their associated Functions.

        Here is an example of the usage and output of this object: (Taken from GroupBy2Test) 

          List sequence0 = Arrays.asList(new Integer[] { 7, 12, 16 });
  List sequence1 = Arrays.asList(new Integer[] { 3, 4, 5 });
  
  Function identity = Function.identity();
  Function times3 = x -> x * 3;
        Parameters:
        entries -
        Returns:
        a n + 1 dimensional tuple, where the first element is the key of the group and the other n entries are lists of objects that are a member of the current group that is being iterated over in the nth list passed in. Note that this is a generator and a n+1 dimensional tuple is yielded for every group. If a list has no members in the current group, GroupBy2.Slot.NONE is returned in place of a generator.

      • drainKey

        private void drainKey(Tuple retVal,
                      int listIdx,
                      R targetVal)
        Each input grouper may generate multiple members which match the specified "targetVal". This method guarantees that all members are added to the list residing at the specified Tuple index.
        Parameters:
        retVal - the Tuple being added to
        listIdx - the index specifying the list within the tuple which will have members added to it
        targetVal - the value to match in order to be an added member
